2 SECTION 1. Arkansas Constitution, Article 5, § 5(c), concerning fiscal
3 sessions of the General Assembly, is amended to read as follows:
4 (c)(1) Beginning in 2010, the General Assembly shall meet in fiscal
5 session on the second Monday in February of each even-numbered year to
6 consider only appropriation bills. The General Assembly may alter the time at
7 which the fiscal session begins.
8 (2)(A) A bill other than an appropriation bill may be considered
9 in a fiscal session if two-thirds (⅔) of the members of each house of the
10 General Assembly approve consideration of the bill the bill is filed during a
11 period beginning seven (7) days before the date the fiscal session begins and
12 ending seven (7) days after the date the fiscal session begins.
13 (B) A bill other than an appropriation bill that is filed
14 outside of the period under subdivision (c)(2)(A) of this section may be
15 considered in a fiscal session if two-thirds (2/3) of the members of each
16 house of the General Assembly approve consideration of the bill.
